"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510097","Department of Health","false","2016-04-19","<p>The information requested is presented in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year Officials Left</p></td><td><p>Number of Resignations</p></td><td><p>Proportion of total staff</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>84</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>55</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>95</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>95</p></td><td><p>5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>91</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The numbers given are for civil servants only. These figures include employees, loans-in from other Government Departments and fixed-term appointments.</p><p>The proportion of staff who resigned is calculated by the total number of resignations in the financial year indicated, divided by the total headcount as at the 31 March of that year.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-04-19T14:11:49.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510097/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510097/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","Department of Health: Resignations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of officials of his Department resigned in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","33292"
