"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510207","Department for International Development","false","2016-04-25","<p>UK aid to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is subject to rigorous scrutiny, with safeguards in place to ensure its being used for proper development purposes. Our financial assistance to the PA is used to pay the salaries of civil servant and pensioners. Our support is provided through a multi-donor trust fund administered by the World Bank, which carries out close monitoring of PA expenditure. Only named civil servants from a pre-approved EU list are eligible, and the vetting process ensures that our funds do not benefit terrorist groups. The process is subject to independent auditing.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2016-04-25T14:46:46.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510207/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510207/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-04-11","Palestinians: Overseas Aid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure that UK aid to Palestine is not given, directly or indirectly, to the families of suicide bombers or to convicted prisoners.","false","Biography information for Baroness Deech",,"Baroness Deech","HL7413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510208","Leader of the House of Lords","false","2016-04-25","<p>As of 21 April, 706 UK statutory instruments had been laid before the House of Commons/Parliament in the 2015-16 session. For completeness, the numbers of statutory instruments laid in previous sessions since 1997 are detailed below:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>1997-98: 1856</p></li><li><p>1998-99: 1479</p></li><li><p>1999-00: 1456</p></li><li><p>2000-01: 868</p></li><li><p>2001-02: 1788</p></li><li><p>2002-03: 1474</p></li><li><p>2003-04: 1281</p></li><li><p>2004-05: 793</p></li><li><p>2005-06: 1885</p></li><li><p>2006-07: 1361</p></li><li><p>2007-08: 1319</p></li><li><p>2008-09: 1302</p></li><li><p>2009-10: 823</p></li><li><p>2010-12: 1809</p></li><li><p>2012-13: 964</p></li><li><p>2013-14: 1173</p></li><li><p>2014-15: 1378</p></li><li><p>2015-16: 706 (so far in this session)</p></li></ul><p> </p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2016-04-25T15:42:57.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510208/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510208/answer",,,,,"92",,"Leader of the House of Lords","2016-04-11","Statutory Instruments","2","House of Lords","To ask the Leader of the House, further to her Written Answer on 17 February (HL5966), how many statutory instruments have now been laid before Parliament in the 2015–16 session to date.","false","Biography information for Lord Dobbs",,"Lord Dobbs","HL7414"
