"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506240","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of jobs estimated to have been created in Wales through European Regional Development Fund projects from the start of the 2007-2013 programmes to the end of February 2016 is 36,400. The number of businesses created in the same period is 11,900.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T16:02:44.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506240/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506240/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","European Regional Development Fund: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) jobs and (b) businesses that have been created in Wales through European Regional Development Fund projects since 2010.","false","Biography information for Yvette Cooper","Normanton, Pontefract and Castleford","Yvette Cooper","33172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506241","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of jobs estimated to have been created in Scotland through European Regional Development Fund projects from the start of the 2007-2013 programmes to the end of February 2016 is 44,311. The number of businesses created in the same period is 17,543.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T16:04:31.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506241/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506241/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","European Regional Development Fund: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) jobs and (b) businesses that have been created in Scotland through European Regional Development Fund projects since 2010.","false","Biography information for Yvette Cooper","Normanton, Pontefract and Castleford","Yvette Cooper","33173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506242","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of jobs estimated to have been created in Yorkshire and the Humber through European Regional Development Fund projects from the start of the 2007-2013 programmes to the end of February 2016 is 20,149. The number of businesses created in the same period is 2,748.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T16:06:14.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506242/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506242/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","European Regional Development Fund: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) jobs and (b) businesses that have been created in Yorkshire and the Humber through European Regional Development Fund projects since 2010.","false","Biography information for Yvette Cooper","Normanton, Pontefract and Castleford","Yvette Cooper","33174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506243","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of jobs estimated to have been created in the North East through European Regional Development Fund projects from the start of the 2007-2013 programmes to the end of February 2016 is 20,602. The number of businesses created in the same period is 5,888.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T16:08:50.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506243/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506243/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","European Regional Development Fund: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) jobs and (b) businesses that have been created in the North East through European Regional Development Fund projects since 2010.","false","Biography information for Yvette Cooper","Normanton, Pontefract and Castleford","Yvette Cooper","33175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506244","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p>The number of jobs estimated to have been created in the North West through European Regional Development Fund projects from the start of the 2007-2013 programmes to the end of February 2016 is 29,795. The number of businesses created in the same period is 9,582.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T16:17:57.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506244/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506244/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","European Regional Development Fund: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) jobs and (b) businesses that have been created in the North West through European Regional Development Fund projects since 2010.","false","Biography information for Yvette Cooper","Normanton, Pontefract and Castleford","Yvette Cooper","33176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506245","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-04-14","<p>The UK Government has not contributed any financial resources to the Your First EURES Job project. As this project is led by the EU Commission, the UK Government does not collect or hold information relating to the number of EU job seekers that have found jobs in the UK, or the number of UK jobseekers that have found work elsewhere in the EU through Your First EURES Job.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-04-14T08:13:50.163Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506245/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506245/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-04-08","Employment Schemes: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much the Government has contributed to the Your first EURES job scheme; how many vacancies have been filled under that scheme in the UK since 2012; and how many UK workers have found work in the EU under that scheme.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","32925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506246","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p>The majority of Alternative Providers remain subject to student number controls, with the exception of nine (as at 12th April 2016) alternative providers that have their own degree awarding powers. It is not possible to determine the impact on national levels of student debt – as any students recruited by these 9 providers may instead have been recruited by providers in the publicly funded sector, none of which are subject to student number controls.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-13T11:37:53.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506246/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506246/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Higher Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of removing student number controls for alternative providers of degree-level courses on national levels of student debt.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","32936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506247","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-04-13T09:03:06.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506247/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506247/answer","UKSA response to 33038 .pdf","UKSA response to 33038 .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Sickness Absence","UKSA Letter to Member - Sickness Absence","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506247/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will estimate the number of days of sickness absence taken for reasons of depression, anxiety or stress in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","33038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506248","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Joint Area Review Delivery Unit supporting the area reviews will arrange for Hon. Members to receive a letter informing them when a review is being launched that covers any part of their constituency and inviting them to give their views.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-18T15:54:02.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506248/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506248/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506248/answer/previousversion/54965","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Further Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 9 November 2015 to Question 13258, whether an hon. Member will be informed about a post-16 area-based review on the basis that their constituency is in the area covered by the review or on the basis that a college in their constituency is included in a review.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","33040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506249","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>Within England, notional allocations for the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF) and European Social Fund (ESF) for the 2014-2020 programming period were made on the basis of Local Enterprise Partnership areas. Transposing these allocations to regional boundaries, the total estimated amount of ERDF and ESF for the 2014-2020 programming period for each region in England is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>East Midlands</p></td><td><p>€598m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East of England</p></td><td><p>€387m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>€762m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East</p></td><td><p>€739m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>€1132</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East</p></td><td><p>€286m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>€1495m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>€909m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Yorkshire and Humber</p></td><td><p>€794m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total for England</p></td><td><p>€6937m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>It should be noted that some Local Enterprise Partnership areas cross the boundaries of regions and therefore the actual spend pattern may not wholly reflect the above notional allocations. Furthermore, Local Enterprise Partnerships and other local partners were asked to suggest the appropriate split between ESF and ERDF in strategies for their area and it is not possible to transpose this accurately to each region.</p><p>The allocations for each year at England level are fixed in the respective programmes for ESF and ERDF.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-18T16:35:07.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506249/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506249/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate his Department has made of the amount of (a) European Regional Development and (b) European Structural funding which will be received by the (i) East Midlands, (ii) East of England, (iii) London, (iv) North East, (v) North West, (vi) South East, (vii) South West, (viii) West Midlands and (ix) Yorkshire and Humber in each year between 2014 and 2020.","false","Biography information for Nick Herbert","Arundel and South Downs","Nick Herbert","33071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506250","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>To complement the work on Women on Boards, Sir John Parker has established a business led diversity initiative to end mono-cultural boards in the FTSE 100 boards by 2020.</p><p>The Government has also asked Baroness McGregor-Smith to undertake a review examining the issues faced by business in developing BME talent from recruitment through to the executive level. She will be reporting findings by the end of 2016.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-18T15:13:04.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506250/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506250/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Directors: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the oral contribution by the Minister for Small Business, Industry and Enterprise on 28 October 2015, Official Report, column 476, if his Department will extend the remit of the Lord Davies review of diversity on boards to include ethnicity.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","33088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506251","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p>Mr Newby has not been involved in the drafting of and consultation process for the Pubs Code.</p><p> </p><p>Officials in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills met the Adjudicator after his appointment to provide him with a high level briefing on Part 4 of the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act and some areas of the draft Pubs Code in order to familiarise him with key aspects ahead of him taking up this important role. During the course of this briefing there was a discussion of some technical aspects of the Market Rent Only arbitration process - for example, the length of time it takes to appoint an independent expert - where the Adjudicator shared his professional insights.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T15:46:26.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506251/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506251/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Pubs Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister for Small Business, Industry and Enterprise of 10 March 2016, Official Report, column 425, in what way Mr Newby has been assisting with the Pubs Code.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","32712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506252","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-13","<p>Mr Newby was appointed in accordance with the Office of the Commissioner for Public Appointments’ (OCPA) Code of Practice for Ministerial Appointments to Public Bodies. As is standard practice, Mr Newby was asked during this appointments process to declare any potential conflicts of interest. The appointment panel discussed conflicts of interest with him at interview. The Panel was satisfied there were no conflicts of interest, and put this advice to ministers.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-13T15:59:49.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506252/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506252/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Pubs Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what methodology the Pubs Code Adjudicator appointment panel employed in order to ensure the appointed Pubs Code Adjudicator had no conflicts of interest.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","32717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506253","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>Information on apprenticeship starts by level and parliamentary constituency are published as a supplementary table (first link) to a Statistical First Release (second link).</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/515077/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-level-and-age.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/515077/apprenticeships-starts-by-geography-level-and-age.xls</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/learner-participation-outcomes-and-level-of-highest-qualification-held" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/learner-participation-outcomes-and-level-of-highest-qualification-held</a></p><p>The term Modern Apprenticeships only applies in Scotland. In England, apprenticeships are described as Intermediate Level, Advanced Level and Higher Apprenticeships.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-18T15:10:17.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506253/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506253/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Apprentices: Dartford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate his Department has made of the number of young people undertaking an (a) modern and (b) higher apprenticeship in Dartford.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","32783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506254","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>Information on Skills Funding Agency spending on the adult skills budget and other programmes is outlined in their Annual Report and Accounts which can be found at the following links:</p><p>2014-15: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015</a></p><p>2013-14: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014</a></p><p>2012-13: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2012-to-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2012-to-2013</a></p><p>2011-12: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2011-to-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2011-to-2012</a></p><p>2010-11: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2010-to-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-skills-funding-agency-annual-report-and-accounts-for-2010-to-2011</a></p><p>2009-10 (Learning and Skills Council): <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-learning-and-skills-councils-annual-report-2009-to-2010" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-learning-and-skills-councils-annual-report-2009-to-2010</a></p><p>The Department collects self-reported data on the ethnicity of further education learners, but not nationality. Learners will be eligible for Skills Funding Agency funding if they are a citizen of a country within the European Economic Area (EEA) and have been resident in the EEA for at least three years prior to the start of learning and are ordinarily resident in England. Training providers are responsible for ensuring that individuals are eligible before claiming funding for them.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-18T15:10:56.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506254/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506254/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Training: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much funding his Department has allocated to publicly-funded training courses through the Skills Funding Agency in each of the last six years; and what proportion of participants in such courses were nationals of (a) the UK, (b) other EU and EEA countries and (c) other countries in each such year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","32797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506255","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-14","<p>HMRC Overseas Trade Statistics on the number of firms trading with the EU are publically available through the UKTradeInfo website.</p><p>HM Treasury estimates that 3.3 million UK jobs are linked to EU exports. Further details are publically available through the GOV.UK Website.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-14T15:56:40.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506255/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506255/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate the number of (a) UK firms that trade with other EU member states and (b) people employed by those firms.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","33212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506256","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-19","<p>My Department does not have any restrictions in place on the import of alleged illegally-mined gold and mineral products from Brazil.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-19T15:24:21.123Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506256/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506256/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Minerals: Brazil","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to prevent the importation to the UK of illegally-mined gold and other mineral products from Brazil.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","33248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506257","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-14","<p>Prison Officers employed in the Scottish Prison Service are members of the Civil Service. Under Schedule 5 of the Scotland Act 1998 the Civil Service is a reserved matter and legislation on pensions and compensation is a matter for Parliament at Westminster.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-14T10:29:42.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506257/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506257/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Prison Officers: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department plans to transfer responsibility for Scottish prison officers' pensions to the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","33249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506258","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 11 April 2016.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T10:09:32.123Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506258/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506258/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Cabinet Office: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he expects to answer Question 26017, tabled by the hon. Member for Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock on 5 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Corri Wilson","Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock","Corri Wilson","33197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506259","Home Office","false","2016-04-15","<p>It is long established Home Office policy not to comment upon matters of personal protective security and their associated costs.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-04-15T13:16:13.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506259/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506259/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-08","Cabinet Office: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much was spent on security for Ministers of her Department entitled to such protection in the last 12 months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","32818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506260","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-14","<p>EROs are already free to work with local schools and colleges in their area and many already do. In addition the Cabinet Office has published a collection of free learning resources aimed at engaging young people in the democratic process. This includes Rock Enrol! which can be used in an educational setting and provides an opportunity for participants to register to vote. The N.I.registration is different from the rest of the UK, so the schools initiative might would not necessarily translate easily across.</p><p> </p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-14T10:27:22.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506260/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506260/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department plans to replicate the Northern Ireland electoral registration/schools initiative before the May 2016 elections and EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","32861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506261","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government has made it easier and more flexible for students to register to vote than ever before with the introduction of online registration. Students are now able to register at both term time and home addresses in just three minutes. Since June 2014, 3.8 million people aged 16-24 have applied to register to vote with 2.8 million of these applications made online. The Government is also working with Higher Education and Further Education bodies including the Association of Colleges and Universities UK to explore voter registration among students further.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-13T14:15:46.983Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506261/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506261/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register: Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans his Department has to encourage voter registration amongst students before the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","32900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506262","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-14","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-04-14T16:27:07.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506262/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506262/answer","UKSA Response to 32897.pdf","UKSA Response to 32897.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - EEA Member Nationals","UKSA Letter to Member - EEA Member Nationals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506262/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Immigrants: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many nationals of other EEA member states migrated to the UK with dependants of school age in the last 12 months; and how many school-aged dependants of nationals of other EEA member states live in the UK.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","32897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506263","Department for Education","false","2016-04-19","<p>Pupil premium eligibility in 2015/16 is based on whether pupils are known to have been looked after by the local authority; have left care through adoption, a special guardianship, child arrangements or residence order; or if a pupil has been registered as eligible for free school meals at any point in the last 6 years. It is not determined through a household income threshold.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-04-19T14:46:46.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506263/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506263/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-04-08","Pupil Premium: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many school-aged pupils there are with at least one parent who is a national in another EEA member state in households with a total income within the threshold for pupil premium eligibility.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","32896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506264","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-19","<p>Since financial year 2012/13 the Cabinet Office has provided funding to local authorities and civil society organisations to support the implementation and delivery of Individual Electoral Registration. Prior to financial year 2010/11 electoral registration policy was under the remit of the Ministry of Justice. The Cabinet Office does not hold any relevant financial data prior to 2010.</p><p>Local Authorities are under a statutory obligation to provide Electoral Registration Officers with funding and resources to support electoral registration more generally. Local Authorities are funded from a block grant that is allocated by the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p><p>The table below notes the funding provided by the Cabinet Office to local authorities and other groups and organisations in Great Britain. This includes core funding to support local authorites in the transition to IER, and the upgrade of hardware, such as printers, to support the new A3 registration forms .The figures also include funding that was allocated to local authorities and other groups to support efforts to increase levels of registration between financial years 2010/11 and 2015/16.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2010-2011</p></td><td><p>2011-2012</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Local Authorities</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£9,115,416</p></td><td><p>£39,537,279</p></td><td><p>£25,858,168</p></td><td><p>£74,510,862</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Other Groups</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£56,545</p></td><td><p>£216,247</p></td><td><p>£1,933,759</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£2,191,401</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p /><p /> <p> </p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-19T16:44:35.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506264/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506264/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the cost of supporting electoral registration by (a) local authorities and (b) other groups was in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","32872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506265","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Government has amended the <a href="http://gov.uk/register-to-vote" target="_blank">gov.uk/register-to-vote</a> site to ensure electors are informed how to register for a postal or proxy vote and of the deadline to register before the upcoming May elections and EU referendum.</p><p> </p><p>Ahead of the referendum registered electors will also receive poll cards informing them how they can apply to vote by post or appoint a proxy.</p><p> </p><p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's overseas network is supporting the Electoral Commission in encouraging British nationals overseas who are eligible to vote to register. This is consistent with previous polls. Expats are encouraged to register as soon as possible and by 16 May at the latest, so that they have time to receive and return their postal ballots ahead of polling day.</p><p> </p><p>We have also extended the electoral timetable which means that postal voting packs can be sent out to voters earlier before polling day, to make it easier for postal votes to be cast successfully.</p><p> </p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T14:21:31.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506265/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506265/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps the Government is taking to encourage people who may not be able to vote in person in the EU referendum to apply for a postal vote before the relevant deadline.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","32873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506266","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>Electoral Registration Officers have a statutory duty to maintain the completeness and accuracy of their registers and are held accountable for meeting performance standards by the Electoral Commission. This includes implementing public engagement strategies to target under registered groups which includes young people. The Government has made available a range of free online learning resources on voter registration. These have been promoted to EROs using channels such as newsletters and Association of Electoral Administrators (AEA) meetings.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-13T14:40:56.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506266/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506266/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how the Government intends to encourage electoral registration officers to prepare and execute strategies to maximise the proportion of (a) 16 and 17 year olds, (b) FE and HE students and (c) people aged 25 years and under registering to vote.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","32874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506267","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-15","<p>The UK Government is committed to delivering the sustainable development goals as agreed by the United Nations in 2015. We will be reviewing the consistency of our plans and policies with the Global Goals.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-04-15T09:49:28.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506267/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506267/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Government Departments: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government has made an assessment of the extent to which the single departmental plans for the current Parliament are consistent with the UK's sustainable development aims.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","32701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506268","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-04-13T12:27:24.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506268/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506268/answer","UKSA response to 32737 .pdf","UKSA response to 32737 .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Deaths by Malnutrition","UKSA Letter to Member - Deaths by Malnutrition","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506268/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Malnutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of deaths in England caused by malnutrition in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","32737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506269","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>A framework of Greening Government Commitments targets for the current Parliament is being considered by Ministers across Government, and an announcement will be made once arrangements are finalised.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T10:08:15.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506269/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506269/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Government Departments: Environment Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to publish the greening government commitments for the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","32669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506270","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The secretariat in Cabinet Office that deals with all European matters reports to the Prime Minister's Adviser on European and Global Issues. Information on Cabinet Office staff and salaries is on <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-structure-charts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-structure-charts</a></p><p>The Government's position, as set out by the Prime Minister to the House on 22 February, is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU. The civil service is working to support the Government’s position.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T10:12:00.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506270/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506270/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 11 February 2016 to Question 26361, how many officials work in the secretariat in the Cabinet Office that deals with all European matters; to whom such officials report; and what such officials' involvement will be in drawing up contingency plans in the event of a UK exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","32678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506271","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government helps promote democratic participation in schools through the Citizenship curriculum. This part of the national curriculum is statutory at Key Stage 3 &amp; 4 and helps to prepare pupils to play a full and active part in society. Pupils learn about democracy, government and how laws are made and upheld. The Government has also developed a number of learning resources, including Rock Enrol! This includes activities that discuss the importance of democratic engagement and can be used with young people in formal and informal educational environments.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-13T14:44:59.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506271/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506271/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to encourage the combination of electoral registration of 16 and 17 year olds with related (a) programmes of study and (b) extra-curricular activities in all English educational establishments.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","33017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506272","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-14","<p>I have considered a range of proposals from local authorities and civil society organisations that could change how registration is currently delivered. The Government is committed to further modernising and improving electoral registration, building on the successful transition to Individual Electoral Registration (IER). We are keen to explore further possibilities in this area but are concerned there may be tension between some forms of automatic registration and the principles underpinning IER, namely individual responsibility and ownership over registering to vote.</p><p> </p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-14T10:26:15.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506272/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506272/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what representations he has (a) received and (b) made on the introduction or piloting of a system of automatic  electoral registration.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","33030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506273","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Democratic Engagement Team, which was created in 2013, has enabled a number of civil society organisations to make an important contribution during the transition to Individual Electoral Registration. Overall, this support has contributed to over 15 million applications to register to vote since June 2014. An overview of the maximising registration funding by year can be found below:</p><p>2012/2013 - £56,545</p><p>2013/2014 - £4.2m</p><p>2014/2015 - £9.8m</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T10:11:07.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506273/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506273/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much funding was (a) allocated and (b) spent by his Department's  Democratic Engagement Team in each of the last six years; and what assessment has been made of the efficiency and effectiveness of that team.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","33031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506274","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>I have considered a range of proposals from local authorities and civil society organisations that could change how registration is currently delivered. The Government is committed to further modernising and improving electoral registration, building on the successful transition to Individual Electoral Registration (IER).</p><p>We are keen to explore further possibilities in this area but are concerned there may be tension between some forms of automatic registration and the principles underpinning IER, namely individual responsibility and ownership over registering to vote.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-04-18T17:00:27.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506274/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506274/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to introduce or pilot a system of automatic electoral registration.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","33032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506275","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>This Government will continue to lead the international agenda to crack down on tax evasion and aggressive tax avoidance. The Summit will address a range of measures to tackle corruption, including promoting transparency. Further information about the London Anti-Corruption Summit can be found on the summit web pages of the <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> website.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-13T08:57:06.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506275/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506275/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether tax avoidance and the role of tax havens is expected to be discussed in plenary at the International Anti-Corruption Summit in London.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","33033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506276","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>On 31 December 2015, the Chancellor announced a review of the tax treatment of airside retail sales, with a view to identifying options for passengers to receive more of the direct benefits. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has completed its initial fact finding.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is keen to identify options that provide overall best value for travellers. This means fully understanding the potential impacts of possible changes on travellers, retailers and airports, and I have asked HMRC to explore these thoroughly. Once this work has been completed, decisions on the best way forward will be made in the autumn.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","32977","2016-04-18T16:02:02.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506276/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506276/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Aviation: VAT Exemptions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects his Department's review of airside VAT-free shopping to be published.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","32976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506277","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>On 31 December 2015, the Chancellor announced a review of the tax treatment of airside retail sales, with a view to identifying options for passengers to receive more of the direct benefits. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has completed its initial fact finding.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is keen to identify options that provide overall best value for travellers. This means fully understanding the potential impacts of possible changes on travellers, retailers and airports, and I have asked HMRC to explore these thoroughly. Once this work has been completed, decisions on the best way forward will be made in the autumn.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","32976","2016-04-18T16:02:03.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506277/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506277/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Aviation: VAT Exemptions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress his Department has made on its review of the treatment of VAT in airside retail shops.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","32977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506278","Prime Minister","false","2016-04-13","I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Denton and Reddish (Mr Gwynne) on 14 January 2016, UIN 21230.","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-04-13T13:27:27.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506278/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506278/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-04-08","Crown Dependencies and British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, which representatives of the UK's Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories the Prime Minister has met since August 2013.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","33054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506279","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>HM Treasury has not made any estimates of the proportion of new buy-to-let mortgage loans over the next five years which will be advanced on a (a) capital repayment and (b) interest-only basis.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-04-13T10:28:30.723Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506279/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506279/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Mortgages","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the proportion of new buy-to-let mortgage loans over the next five years which will be advanced on an (a) capital repayment and (b) interest-only basis.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","32960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506280","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>Information about the London Anti-Corruption Summit can be found on the summit web pages of the GOV.UK website. Further details about the summit will be announced in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-13T08:59:54.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506280/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506280/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to publish a draft agenda for the Anti-Corruption Summit to be held in May 2016.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","33021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506281","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-20","<p>No assessment has been made of the potential incidence of employers hiring more apprentices to avoid paying the national minimum wage.</p><p>The current minimum wage rate for an apprentice is £3.30 per hour. This applies to apprentices who are aged under 19 or those in the first year of their Apprenticeship. Apprentices aged 19 or above and in the second year of their apprenticeship must be paid at least the minimum wage rate that relates to their age. This means an apprentice aged 25 or above in the second year must be paid at least the National Living Wage.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-20T15:03:52.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506281/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506281/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Apprentices: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to paragraph 2.48 of the National Minimum Wage Low Pay Commission Report Spring 2016, Cm 9207, what assessment he has made of the potential incidence of employers hiring apprentices to avoid paying the new higher minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","33085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506282","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-04-18","<p>The amount Defra has accrued for each of the last ten financial years following the conclusion of EU audits is shown in the table below. These figures relate to a number of different Common Agricultural Policy (CAP) schemes over a number of historical scheme years as disallowance is paid in arrears.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="10"><p>Disallowance (*) £millions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>05/06</p></td><td><p>06/07</p></td><td><p>07/08</p></td><td><p>08/09</p></td><td><p>09/10</p></td><td><p>10/11</p></td><td><p>11/12</p></td><td><p>12/13</p></td><td><p>13/14</p></td><td><p>14/15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>63</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>162**</p></td><td><p>181</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>81</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>(*) Reflects the sums the European Commission has ruled cannot be reimbursed (i.e. the amounts they have “disallowed”).</p><p> </p><p>(**) Includes £11million in disallowance relating to Northern Ireland. All other figures relate to England only. The Devolved Administrations are now responsible for disallowance relating to their administration of the CAP.</p><p> </p><p>The Department’s Annual Report and Accounts in 2014/15 provides provisions of £64.5million for future disallowance related to historical audits. Future disallowance penalties are difficult to predict. However, the Department’s aim is to reduce disallowance to as low a level as possible and we expect a return to disallowance of about 2 per cent of scheme value by 2019.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","33012","2016-04-18T13:40:48.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506282/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506282/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-04-08","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what total amount of disallowance penalties was imposed on the UK by the EU in each of the last 10 years; and what contingency funding has been set aside for disallowance penalties in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","33004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506283","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-13","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-04-13T12:29:58.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506283/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506283/answer","UKSA response to 33167 ANNEX .xlsx ; UKSA response to 33167.pdf","UKSA response to 33167 ANNEX .xlsx ; UKSA response to 33167.pdf","Excel Attachment for Member - Jobs Created ; UKSA Letter to Member - Jobs Created","Excel Attachment for Member - Jobs Created ; UKSA Letter to Member - Jobs Created","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506283/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-08","Job Creation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many new jobs have been created in each region and constituent part of the UK since 2010.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","33167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506284","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) applies HM Treasury’s long term discount rate to calculate the carrying value of English student loans shown in the BIS financial statements.</p><p> </p><p>Loans issued by devolved administrations are shown in their respective financial statements. The accounting treatment and discount rates applied are a matter for them.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury is always open to discussion with the devolved administrations about such matters.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","33223","2016-04-13T10:25:46.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506284/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506284/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with his counterparts in the devolved administrations on the Government's change to the discount rate applied to student loans.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","33215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506285","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government has made no specific estimates of the number of people who will pay less Inheritance Tax in either Ashfield constituency or Nottinghamshire as a result of the reforms to Inheritance Tax that will be introduced from April 2017.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-13T16:22:24.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506285/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506285/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Inheritance Tax: Nottinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of people in (a) Ashfield constituency and (b) Nottinghamshire who will pay less inheritance tax as a result of the proposed changes to inheritance tax thresholds planned to be introduced from 2017.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","33225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506286","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>Statistics on the number of estates liable to Inheritance Tax, broken down by Westminster Parliamentary Constituency, are published annually. The most recent update covered deaths in 2012-13 and can be found online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/inheritance-tax-statistics-table-1212-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2012-to-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/inheritance-tax-statistics-table-1212-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2012-to-2013</a>.</p><p> </p><p>A previous update covering 2011-12 deaths can be found online at <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20150131092906/https:/www.gov.uk/government/statistics/inheritance-tax-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2010-to-2011-by-regions-and-parliamentary-constituencies" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20150131092906/https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/inheritance-tax-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2010-to-2011-by-regions-and-parliamentary-constituencies</a>, and an earlier update covering 2010-11 deaths can be found online at <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140321030529/https:/www.gov.uk/government/publications/inheritance-tax-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2010-to-2011-by-regions-and-parliamentary-constituencies" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140321030529/https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/inheritance-tax-provisional-numbers-of-taxpaying-estates-passing-on-death-in-2010-to-2011-by-regions-and-parliamentary-constituencies</a>.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-13T16:25:42.103Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506286/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506286/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Inheritance Tax: Ashfield","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Ashfield constituency paid inheritance tax in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","33226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506287","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) applies HM Treasury’s long term discount rate to calculate the carrying value of English student loans shown in the BIS financial statements.</p><p> </p><p>Loans issued by devolved administrations are shown in their respective financial statements. The accounting treatment and discount rates applied are a matter for them.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury is always open to discussion with the devolved administrations about such matters.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","33215","2016-04-13T10:25:46.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506287/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506287/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the change to the discount rate applied to student loans applies to all parts of the UK.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","33223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506288","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-14","<p>The Department does not collate data on the value of the total contribution that arms exports make to the UK economy. However, we do publish official statistics on defence exports, which show that the UK’s defence export total in 2014 was an estimated £8.5bn. Further details of defence exports can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-defence-and-security-export-figures-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-defence-and-security-export-figures-2014</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","33244","2016-04-14T16:02:50.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506288/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506288/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506288/answer/previousversion/54964","Biography information for Anna Soubry","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-08","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the contribution of the arms export industry to the UK economy in 2014.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","33221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506289","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government is committed to supporting homeowners. One part of this commitment is ensuring that there is a level playing field between homeowners and landlords. In the 2015 Autumn Statement, we announced a 3 percentage point increase in the rates of Stamp Duty Land Tax applying to the purchase of additional residential properties, such as second homes and buy-to-let properties; and in the Summer Budget of 2015, we acted to restrict, to the basic rate of income tax, the tax relief on finance costs received by landlords of residential property.</p><p> </p><p>The Financial Policy Committee recently stated that the combination of forthcoming changes to mortgage interest tax relief and the implementation of the PRA Supervisory Statement will probably dampen growth of buy-to-let mortgage lending relative to lenders’ plans.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-04-13T10:11:30.563Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506289/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506289/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Mortgages","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Prudential Regulation Authority's Draft Supervisory Statement on Buy-to-Let Underwriting Standards, published in March 2016, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the 20 per cent growth in buy-to-let mortgage lending over the next three years on home ownership.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","33114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506290","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government will publicise the Tax-Free Childcare (TFC) scheme in good time ahead of its introduction through a range of digital and print channels. HMRC will also work with the childcare industry and representative groups who interact regularly with parents to raise awareness of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs is developing an online childcare calculator to help parents understand their eligibility for government childcare support. From early 2017, parents of the youngest children will be able to enter the scheme first, with all eligible parents brought in by the end of 2017. Parents will not be able to open childcare accounts prior to the launch of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>TFC will be straightforward and quick to apply online for the vast majority of parents. We estimate that up to 9% of the families eligible for the scheme of that population may have issues with either accessing or using the internet. HM Revenue and Customs will ensure that assistance is provided, usually by telephone, so these families do not miss out on the support available.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare is part of the wider government childcare offer which will be worth over £6Bn per annum and together provide generous support to families on all levels of income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","33078 ; 33080 ; 33081 ; 33131","2016-04-13T16:05:39.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506290/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506290/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of parents eligible for tax-free childcare who do not have access to the internet; and what plans he has to ensure all such families are not excluded from access to tax-free childcare due to lack of access to the internet.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","33079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506291","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government will publicise the Tax-Free Childcare (TFC) scheme in good time ahead of its introduction through a range of digital and print channels. HMRC will also work with the childcare industry and representative groups who interact regularly with parents to raise awareness of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs is developing an online childcare calculator to help parents understand their eligibility for government childcare support. From early 2017, parents of the youngest children will be able to enter the scheme first, with all eligible parents brought in by the end of 2017. Parents will not be able to open childcare accounts prior to the launch of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>TFC will be straightforward and quick to apply online for the vast majority of parents. We estimate that up to 9% of the families eligible for the scheme of that population may have issues with either accessing or using the internet. HM Revenue and Customs will ensure that assistance is provided, usually by telephone, so these families do not miss out on the support available.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare is part of the wider government childcare offer which will be worth over £6Bn per annum and together provide generous support to families on all levels of income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","33078 ; 33079 ; 33081 ; 33131","2016-04-13T16:05:39.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506291/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506291/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of parents who will not be eligible for tax-free childcare as a result of the decision to (a) lower the upper income limit per parent from £150,000 to £100,000 and (b) increase the minimum income level per parent from the equivalent of eight hours to 16 hours at the national living wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","33080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506292","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government will publicise the Tax-Free Childcare (TFC) scheme in good time ahead of its introduction through a range of digital and print channels. HMRC will also work with the childcare industry and representative groups who interact regularly with parents to raise awareness of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs is developing an online childcare calculator to help parents understand their eligibility for government childcare support. From early 2017, parents of the youngest children will be able to enter the scheme first, with all eligible parents brought in by the end of 2017. Parents will not be able to open childcare accounts prior to the launch of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>TFC will be straightforward and quick to apply online for the vast majority of parents. We estimate that up to 9% of the families eligible for the scheme of that population may have issues with either accessing or using the internet. HM Revenue and Customs will ensure that assistance is provided, usually by telephone, so these families do not miss out on the support available.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare is part of the wider government childcare offer which will be worth over £6Bn per annum and together provide generous support to families on all levels of income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","33078 ; 33079 ; 33080 ; 33131","2016-04-13T16:05:39.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506292/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506292/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans his Department has to raise awareness of tax-free childcare with parents before that scheme is launched in early 2017.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","33081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506293","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>Our priority for all the Overseas Territories that function with financial centres such as the British Virgin Islands has been for them to hold accurate and current beneficial ownership information on island in central registers or the equivalent, where they do not already do so, and to allow for UK law enforcement to access that information. The arrangement signed with the British Virgin Islands achieves this and represents a significant step forward in our ability to counter criminal activity and should be welcomed.</p><p>As the Prime Minister, the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) said in the House on 11 April, only about three countries in the world, including Britain, are implementing publically accessible central registers of company beneficial ownership information. If we had tried to push that on to the British Virgin Islands and other Overseas Territories straightaway, we would not have got nearly as far as we have. The actions taken by the British Virgin Islands and the other Overseas Territories puts them well ahead of many of our international partners.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-04-18T13:16:12.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506293/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506293/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-04-08","British Virgin Islands: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to require companies registered in the British Virgin Islands to publish details of all significant and beneficial owners and to place all such information on an online searchable register.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","33190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506294","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Overseas Territories are separate jurisdictions with their own democratically elected governments under which they are responsible for company law.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-04-18T13:17:08.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506294/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506294/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-04-08","British Overseas Territories: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to require all companies registered in British Overseas Territories to publish detailed annual accounts.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","33191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506295","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Overseas Territories are separate jurisdictions with their own democratically elected governments under which they are responsible for company law.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-04-18T14:39:56.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506295/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506295/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-04-08","British Overseas Territories: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to prohibit the use of nominee directors for companies registered in British Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","33192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506296","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The National Mesothelioma Centre will be a collaboration between four leading institutions who have a major interest in the treatment of mesothelioma: National Heart and Lung Institute (NHLI) at Imperial College; Royal Brompton Hospital; Institute of Cancer Research (ICR); and Royal Marsden Hospital. This collaboration will form the hub of the Centre which will engage with all other hospitals in the UK to which mesotheliomas are referred and treated.</p><p>Professor Sir Anthony Newton Taylor, Head of Research &amp; Development at the National Heart &amp; Lung Institute, who made the application for support from LIBOR fines, is working closely with the British Lung Foundation and other charities in order to ensure that experts from across the lung and cancer research community are able to contribute to this important enterprise.</p><p>The £5 million grant, which is intended as seed funding, has been profiled over 4 years and will be paid to the National Mesothelioma Centre, once established. The funding will be subjected to standard Grant Terms and Conditions, including a feedback and reporting mechanism, and audit.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","33076 ; 33077","2016-04-13T10:22:35.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506296/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506296/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Mesothelioma","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what consultation took place with mesothelioma charities and other organisations before the announcement of the establishment of the National Mesothelioma Centre in Budget 2016.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","33075"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506297","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-26","<p>Around 7m people are receiving Child Benefit. To extract and collate the value of all payments made to EU migrants for children living outside the UK in the format requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Information relating to the number of Child Benefit claims paid to families with children living overseas is available in the Government publication , “The best of both worlds: the United Kingdom's special status in a reformed European Union”. This publication is available on Gov.uk</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-best-of-both-worlds-the-united-kingdoms-special-status-in-a-reformed-european-union" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-best-of-both-worlds-the-united-kingdoms-special-status-in-a-reformed-european-union</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government’s new settlement between the UK and the EU means that EU nationals whose children live abroad will ultimately receive Child Benefit at a rate that reflects the conditions – including the standard of living and child benefit paid – of the country where their child lives. This will restore fairness to the system.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","32686","2016-04-26T15:58:39.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506297/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506297/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Child Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 17 March 2016 to Question 27522, on child benefit: immigrants, and with reference to the Answer of 22 October 2012, Official Report, columns 619-20, on child benefit: EU nationals, and the Answer of 6 September 2010, Official Report, columns 189-90, on benefits: British nationals abroad, how many child benefit awards there were for children living in each non-UK country in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","33108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506298","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The National Mesothelioma Centre will be a collaboration between four leading institutions who have a major interest in the treatment of mesothelioma: National Heart and Lung Institute (NHLI) at Imperial College; Royal Brompton Hospital; Institute of Cancer Research (ICR); and Royal Marsden Hospital. This collaboration will form the hub of the Centre which will engage with all other hospitals in the UK to which mesotheliomas are referred and treated.</p><p>Professor Sir Anthony Newton Taylor, Head of Research &amp; Development at the National Heart &amp; Lung Institute, who made the application for support from LIBOR fines, is working closely with the British Lung Foundation and other charities in order to ensure that experts from across the lung and cancer research community are able to contribute to this important enterprise.</p><p>The £5 million grant, which is intended as seed funding, has been profiled over 4 years and will be paid to the National Mesothelioma Centre, once established. The funding will be subjected to standard Grant Terms and Conditions, including a feedback and reporting mechanism, and audit.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","33075 ; 33077","2016-04-13T10:22:35.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506298/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506298/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Mesothelioma","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 2.15 of Budget 2016, what criteria were or will be applied in the selection of organisations to participate in the National Mesothelioma Centre.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","33076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506299","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Government will publicise the Tax-Free Childcare (TFC) scheme in good time ahead of its introduction through a range of digital and print channels. HMRC will also work with the childcare industry and representative groups who interact regularly with parents to raise awareness of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs is developing an online childcare calculator to help parents understand their eligibility for government childcare support. From early 2017, parents of the youngest children will be able to enter the scheme first, with all eligible parents brought in by the end of 2017. Parents will not be able to open childcare accounts prior to the launch of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>TFC will be straightforward and quick to apply online for the vast majority of parents. We estimate that up to 9% of the families eligible for the scheme of that population may have issues with either accessing or using the internet. HM Revenue and Customs will ensure that assistance is provided, usually by telephone, so these families do not miss out on the support available.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare is part of the wider government childcare offer which will be worth over £6Bn per annum and together provide generous support to families on all levels of income.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","33079 ; 33080 ; 33081 ; 33131","2016-04-13T16:05:38.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506299/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506299/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-08","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department plans to produce an online tool to allow parents to compare the benefits of tax-free childcare with other childcare support schemes.","false","Biography information for Cather