"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506363","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-14","<p>This Government has demonstrated its commitment to our Special Forces by announcing a £2 billion programme of investment over the course of this Parliament. All military operations, including the activities of the Special Forces, are discussed and scrutinised at the highest levels of Government, including at the National Security Council. However, as it is the longstanding policy of the Government not to comment on our Special Forces, or to release information relating to them, I cannot comment on specific questions about personnel, equipment, discussions or activities in relation to these units.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","32787 ; 32788 ; 32789 ; 32790 ; 32791 ; 32792 ; 32793","2016-04-14T15:57:55.34Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506363/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506363/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","Special Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether special forces deployments are discussed at meetings of the National Security Council.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","32773"
