"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506371","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-14","<p>Italy is leading the planning for a Libya International Assistance Mission which is intended to provide training to Libyan security forces in response to a formal request made by the Libyan Government of National Accord. The mission is not designed to provide security for the Libyan Government.</p><p>The capabilities, troop numbers and objectives for any potential deployment are not yet sufficiently developed and will be further refined once a request for support has been received and the requirement becomes clear. No decisions have been made about the contribution of any British military forces to this mission.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-04-14T15:58:26.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506371/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506371/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","Libya: International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the capabilities, troop numbers and mission objectives of the Libya international assistance mission.","false","Biography information for Adam Holloway","Gravesham","Adam Holloway","32745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506372","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-13","<p>When deploying to the Far East Royal Naval vessels would normally have access to the port facility of the nation that they visit during the deployment.</p><p>In addition, the United Kingdom operates a jetty and fuel depot at Sembawang in Singapore as part of our commitment to the Five Powers Defence Arrangements.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-04-13T14:32:58.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506372/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506372/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","Navy: Far East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what facilities are currently available to the Royal Navy in the Far East.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","32723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506373","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-13","<p>During my visit I had discussions with senior Saudi leadership on a range of defence and security issues, including the importance of International Humanitarian Law. The government of Saudi Arabia is well aware of our views on human rights and our opposition to the death penalty. Our expectation remains that these three individuals will not be executed.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-04-13T16:34:03.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506373/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506373/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","Saudi Arabia: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether during his meeting with Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia Mohammed bin Naif bin Abdulaziz in Riyadh on 28 March 2016 he (a) discussed human rights in that country (b) made representations about Ali a Nimr, Dawood al Mahroon and Abdullah al Zaher.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506374","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no plans to publish CarillionAmey's (CA) Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) externally.</p><p> </p><p>However letters are sent out each month as part of a wider Accommodation performance update to key stakeholders, including the Families Federations. These letters report on the following national housing prime contract KPIs.</p><p> </p><p>Service Family Accommodation (SFA) allocations;</p><p>Void property preparation;</p><p>Move-in;</p><p>Helpdesk telephone response;</p><p>Reactive maintenance;</p><p>Statutory and Mandatory checks; and</p><p>Stage 1 complaints.</p><p> </p><p>CA have not met all their KPIs since contract award, however the Department has now installed a comprehensive plan in this and other contracts which CA are responsible for which has meant that as of March the vast majority of national housing prime contract KPIs are now being met or exceeded.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-04-18T16:18:34.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506374/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506374/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","CarillionAmey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to publish (a) CarillionAmey's key performance indicators (KPIs) and (b) his Department's assessment of the extent to which those KPIs have been met in each year of the present contract.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","33020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506375","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-14","<p>On 31 January 2016, CarillionAmey were responsible for managing 46,911 Service Family Accommodation properties on behalf of the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-04-14T16:02:25.363Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506375/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506375/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","CarillionAmey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many properties are managed by CarillionAmey on behalf of his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","33018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506376","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-14","<p>The National Housing Prime contract was fully implemented on 1 December 2014 replacing the previous separate UK arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>On that date, CarillionAmey became responsible for the repair and maintenance service. The number of maintenance requests received from that date (by month) is shown in the following table:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Financial Year 2014-15</p></td><td><p>Financial Year 2015-16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>21,585</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>20,020</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>21,213</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>22,144</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>20,945</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>24,224</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>23,185</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p>23,627</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December</p></td><td><p>13,493</p></td><td><p>24,648</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January</p></td><td><p>23,205</p></td><td><p>24,634</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February</p></td><td><p>25,188</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March</p></td><td><p>23,520</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Totals</p></td><td><p>85,406</p></td><td><p>226,225</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Data is not yet available for February or March of financial year 2015-16.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-04-14T16:02:03.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506376/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/506376/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-08","CarillionAmey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence,